@startuml
title Provider Routing by Domain

skinparam packageStyle rectangle

package "cell_biology" {
  [Consensus]
  [Semantic Scholar]
  [Europe PMC]
  [NCBI fallback]
  [ATCC / Thermo / Promega / Sigma]
  [protocols.io]
  [OpenWetWare]
}

package "diagnostics_biosensor" {
  [Consensus]
  [Semantic Scholar]
  [Europe PMC]
  [arXiv fallback]
  [NCBI biomedical fallback]
  [Tavily supplier search]
  [protocols.io]
}

package "animal_gut_health" {
  [Consensus]
  [Semantic Scholar]
  [Europe PMC]
  [NCBI fallback]
  [protocols.io]
  [OpenWetWare fallback]
}

package "microbial_electrochemistry" {
  [Consensus]
  [Semantic Scholar]
  [Europe PMC]
  [arXiv fallback]
  [protocols.io]
  [supplier search if explicit need]
}

note bottom
Semantic Scholar and Europe PMC are always primary Literature QC providers.
NCBI and arXiv are route-specific fallbacks.
EvidencePack then adds protocol, supplier, standards, and inferred layers.
end note

@enduml
